reviewText: The PJs is a funny series, it was made back when being funny was the most important thing in a comedy series.  You connect more to it if you have a relation to the project but even if you don't, you'll still laugh.  Think Good Times without being so preachy.
summary: Scathingly funny, brilliant writing - But definitely NOT PC
Title: The PJ's: Season 3

reviewText: The PJs started as a biting social animated comedy and maintained that through the first two seasons. By the third season, the impact of PC censors took out some of the bite out of the comedy. The resulting third season is more reserved but still funny. Still, this is still very funny!
summary: Slightly watered down humor still delivers
Title: The PJ's: Season 3

reviewText: The PJ's: The 3rd and final season is just greatly excellent and funny. Eddie Murphy who created the TV Series did a excellent job as the voice-over of Thurgoode Stubbs who is cheif superentent of the Hilton Jacobs Projects.
